bug.short_desc: Static initializer in enum after 2000th enum constant will not be generated

long_desc.thetext: Thanks for the patch! I will take this forward.

I could not reproduce in latest. This looks like a duplicate of bug 350095 which has been fixed for 3.7.1.
What build are you using ?

(In reply to comment #2) > I could not reproduce in latest. > This looks like a duplicate of bug 350095 which has been fixed for 3.7.1. > > What build are you using ?
We could reproduce this in Helios (JDT 3.8.1/3.8.2), Indigo (3.7.0). I debugged the Indigo JDT and could see that the code for generating static fields/initializer for enum with an amount of more then 2000 constants will not be executed.
After patching the Clinit.java the field/initializer would be generated (checked with jad).

Thanks for the patch, Olivier! I have released the patch here:
http://git.eclipse.org/c/jdt/eclipse.jdt.core.git/commit/?id=8aab6b334c56ea22c179215ade8ac8c0a3d89d22
I have released the test in a separate commit. Will push the fix for 3.8.2 and also consider it fix for R3_7_maintenance.
Fix and test released in R3_8_maintenance for 3.8 M2
